cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.IR. 

This paper proposes an approach that uses object segmentation and convolutional neural networks to improve object detection accuracy. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves the use of deep neural networks, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves the use of image and video processing techniques, which could place it in cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper involves the use of inference in a Markov Random Field, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
